\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ordained? And by His command both evil and good come. But “why should a living man complain? A 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ man for his sins.” Every man should complain about his sins, because they are what bring the evil 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ upon him. (\lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ By the command of the Most High, neither good nor evil come\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  Said Rabbi Johanan: 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ Since the day that the Holy One, blessed be He, said, [Deut. 30:15]: “See, I have set before you today 
